**Overview**

This dashboard provides information about the File Integrity Monitoring events collected.  

The FIM integration sends events when a file is changed (created, updated, or deleted) in realtime. At startup this integration will perform an initial scan of the configured files and directories to generate baseline data for the monitored paths and detect changes since the last time it was run. It uses locally persisted data in order to only send events for new or modified files.

This integration is compatible with Linux, Windows and macOS platforms.

More information at the [**Integration Page**](/app/integrations/detail/fim/overview).
